Answer: W 3 1

Here’s the reasoning:  
• Row3 is very light on defense (its only plant is a  sunflower at col0, which won’t shoot);  
• With 130 sun available, buying a 100‐sun Peashooter can be used to help protect this vulnerable lane when the next zombie spawns;  
• Placing the Peashooter at row3, column1 lets it start attacking earlier while leaving the leftmost cell (col0) already occupied by a Sunflower, ensuring the new shooter has more turns to fire before a zombie reaches it.
